# Roadmap Data Model

The **roadmap** is the user-facing course structure in the EWA app. It is built from the same entities available through `courses-admin-api` tools, but assembled differently for the end user.

## Roadmap vs Admin API

| Aspect            | Roadmap (user-facing)               | Admin API (this plugin)                |
|-------------------|--------------------------------------|----------------------------------------|
| Audience          | Mobile app user                      | Content team / AI agent                |
| Data shape        | Flat list with progress              | Hierarchical CRUD                      |
| Lessons           | Only `isReady` + matching language   | All lessons, any status                |
| Exercises         | Full content, resolved media URLs    | Metadata + content                     |
| User progress     | Included (scores, completion)        | Not available                          |
| Write operations  | None                                 | None (spec is read-only)               |

## Data graph

The roadmap assembles data top-down:

```
Section
  └── Unit
        └── Lesson
              ├── LessonWord   (vocabulary items for the lesson)
              ├── LessonPhrase (phrases / dialogues)
              └── Exercise
                    ├── Word    (linked word data)
                    └── Sample  (audio sample → resolved URL)
```

### Section → Unit → Lesson

Same entities as in the admin API hierarchy. The roadmap filters by:
- `learningLanguage` matching user's learning language
- `isDeleted = false`
- `isReady[lang] = true` for the user's native language
- Sorted by `number`

### Lesson → LessonWord

`LessonWord` connects lessons to vocabulary:
- `lessonId` → parent lesson
- `wordId` → `Word` entity (translations, transcription, audio, examples)
- Each lesson can have 0–N words
- Words are loaded separately from exercises

### Lesson → LessonPhrase

`LessonPhrase` holds dialogue lines and phrases:
- `lessonId` → parent lesson
- Contains text, translations, audio references
- Used in `dialogues` and `aiDialogue` lesson kinds

### Exercise → Word

Exercises of vocabulary type reference a `Word` via `exercise.word` (UUID).
The Word entity contains:
- `origin` (the word itself)
- `meanings` (per-language translations)
- `transcription`
- `audio` (pronunciation URL)
- `examples` (usage sentences)

### Exercise → Sample

Exercises can reference an audio/video `Sample`:
- `exercise.sample` → Sample UUID
- Resolved to `exercise.videoUrl` at runtime
- Used for listening exercises, video-based exercises

## Key lesson kinds in roadmap

| Kind           | What the user sees                    | Content source                |
|----------------|---------------------------------------|-------------------------------|
| `common`       | Mixed exercises (default)             | Manual + AI                   |
| `words`        | Vocabulary drills                     | LessonWords                   |
| `texts`        | Reading comprehension                 | LessonPhrases                 |
| `dialogues`    | Pre-scripted dialogue practice        | LessonPhrases + Samples       |
| `aiDialogue`   | AI-generated conversation             | LLM-generated at runtime      |
| `chatTests`    | Chat-based level assessment           | Exercises (chat format)       |

## CEFR / GSE mapping

Lessons and grammar topics are tagged with CEFR levels and GSE (Global Scale of English) ranges:

| CEFR | GSE Range | EWA languageLevel     |
|------|-----------|------------------------|
| Pre-A1 | 10–21   | `initial`              |
| A1   | 22–29     | `beginner`             |
| A2   | 30–42     | `elementary`           |
| B1   | 43–58     | `preIntermediate`      |
| B2   | 59–75     | `intermediate` / `upperIntermediate` |
| C1   | 76–84     | `advanced`             |
| C2   | 85–90     | `advanced`             |

Use `list_grammar(cefr="A1")` or `list_grammar(gseMin=22, gseMax=29)` to explore grammar at a specific level.
